{"id":4921,"count":4,"description":"<h2>Uzbekistan<\/h2>\r\nDiscover spectacular Uzbekistan, the jewel of the silk road, and one of the most astonishingly beautiful destinations on the planet. Tourism is relatively new to the country and, as a result, the hospitality of the local people is overwhelming. Experience the journey of a lifetime through a variety of phenomenal landscapes from east to west. All the while making memories and friends that will last forever.\r\n<h3>Turquoise Cities<\/h3>\r\nVariety is the spice of life in Uzbekistan, a landlocked country with a remarkable diversity in its scenery. From the beautiful green mountain valleys and contemporary cities in the east to the sandy deserts and magnificent fortresses of the west. The one constant, however, is a horizon dotted with the endless turquoise blue domes of stunning mosques, palaces, and madrassas. The cities that are home to these architectural beauties are a time capsule to a fascinating past. Enter through fort walls that protect these magical cities, to discover sensational golds, oranges, and blues of mesmerizing palaces, religious relics, and squares.\r\n<h3>Dazzling Details<\/h3>\r\nThe beauty is in the details everywhere in Uzbekistan. In the detailed soviet mosaics on many walls in Tashkent. In the intricate patterns of the tiles, or carved wood, and in the rainbow colors of market fruit and veg. The best way to discover these wonders is to travel the length of the country via train. This is an amazing way to sightsee, and also stop off at the legendary silk road cities of <a href=\"https:\/\/www.saltinourhair.com\/uzbekistan\/samarkand-uzbekistan\/\">Samarkand<\/a>, <a href=\"https:\/\/www.saltinourhair.com\/uzbekistan\/bukhara-uzbekistan\/\">Bukhara<\/a>, and <a href=\"https:\/\/www.saltinourhair.com\/uzbekistan\/khiva-uzbekistan\/\">Khiva<\/a>. It\u2019s not in many places that you\u2019ll find such breathtaking beauty, the most welcoming people, and captivating history.","link":"http